if you could go back in time to spend one day with a relative friend who passed away who would you spend the day with and what would you do i would spend the day with my father and we'd go for a motorcycle ride and picnic spend the day with my brother roy and tell him how much i'd always loved him and thank him for always having been good to me and ask him to forgive me for the times i took for granted between us which i did not truly believe would come interrupted so soon by death and if i could add another person also recently passed that would be granduncle bob i'd say to him that i was sorry i had not been able to send him brownies the moist kind which he preferred since as i prepared to make them and send them he died days later i cry every time i remember these missed times now not to be possible forever Roy Orbison Bob and George About a Boy Sola fide Sleeping Murder Sin Jewish bereavement Recess (TV series) Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Mojave people John F. Kennedy assassination Knots Landing The McGuire Sisters John the Baptist The Beatles discography Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Love and Theft The Amber Spyglass One Tree Hill (TV series) Edward VIII of the United Kingdom EastEnders The Brothers Karamazov John Berryman Bob Rae Oasis (band) Mnemonic Jon Secada Time Out of Mind Miss Saigon Eid ul-Fitr Charlie Brown Priesthood (Mormonism) RuneScape gods Cliff Richard Peter Pan The Times They Are A-Changin' Le Malade imaginaire Social rule 613 mitzvot Kenny McCormick Shaggy dog story Bread Pitaten Joseph (Hebrew Bible) Billboard Hot 100 Theodore Roosevelt Franklin (television series) American Pie (song) Reincarnation The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Have I Got News For You Random Harvest Aida (musical) The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Jacob Walt Disney Japanese funeral Days of our Lives Duane Allman Trailer Park Boys New Morning Louis XV of France Cenodoxus Battles of Lexington and Concord HTTP cookie Oh My